com.bmd.android.collection.iterator

Interface SparseIterable<E>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<E>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BooleanSparseIterable, ElementSparseIterable<E>, IntSparseIterable, LongSparseArrayIterable<V>, LongSparseIterable, SimpleArrayMapIterable<K,V>, SparseArrayCompatIterable<V>, SparseArrayIterable<V>, SparseBooleanArrayIterable, SparseIntArrayIterable, SparseLongArrayIterable, SupportLongSparseArrayIterable<V>

    public interface SparseIterable<E>
extends Iterable<E>
    This interface defines the base functionalities of an Iterable wrapping an Android sparse collection, such as SparseArray and SparseArrayCompat.

    Created by davide on 3/10/14.

    See Also:
    AndroidCollections

      • firstPositionOf

        int firstPositionOf(Object element)
        Finds the position of the first element, in the iteration order, equal to the specified one.

        Note that the returned value is relative to the iterator cycles so, in case filters has been applied to this iterable, the returned number might not match with the index in the sparse collection.

        Parameters:
        element - The element to search for.
        Returns:
        The position in the iteration, or -1 if the object is not found.
